Overview

Getting Started

We will first load the required packages using the below code chunk. We will start off by using ggstatsplot and tidyverse

packages = c('tidyverse','ggstatsplot')
for(p in packages){
  if(!require(p, character.only = T)){
    install.packages(p)
  }
  library(p, character.only = T)
}

Importing data

exam <- read_csv("data/Exam_data.csv")

Working with ggstatsplot

ANOVA Test

ggbetweenstats(
  data = exam,
  x = RACE,
